wikipedia_page.main: Fred Higgins is an English former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1940s and 1950s. He played at representative level for Great Britain and England, and at club level for Widnes, as a second-row, i.e. number 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums. He also appeared for Wigan as a World War II guest player.
